Republicans threaten to disrupt America

iolent criminal offend-
ers, your days are num-
bered! Welfare recipi-

ents, this Christmas thank God
for all the big checks you’ve
received from the government.
Your days of getting money to
smoke dope and make babies
are over!!! And to you young
healthy sixty-five-year—old
grandparents, did you really
think that you’d get a social
security check so soon? Get
out and work five more years
and maybe you’ll live to see a
social security check! And if
not, you know the rules: “Two
things are sure in this life -
death and taxes!” Buckle your
seatbelts tight, America! The
Republicans are now at the
wheel! Wow.

Thank God the elections are
over. All through the months
before the election, there was a
steady stream of propaganda
ﬂowing out of the speakers of
our televisions and radios.
Propaganda about crime.
Propaganda about welfare.
Propaganda about the sixties’
“Great Society “ programs and
how debilitating these pro-
grams have been to the econo-
my. Of course, as with most
propaganda there is some truth
in these ideas. The problem is
that it’s not the whole truth.

Often when these slippery,
slick, designer politicians talk

about an issue, only part of the ‘

issue is presented. For exam-
ple, every third politician talks
tough on the crime issue. We’ll
hear things like, “We don’t
make any excuses for violent
criminals. If a person or per-
sons commit a violent crime,
they will go to jail for life.”
Lately this has been played
over and over again in the ears
of the people so much that it
seems like a tough-talking
tournament.

The sad thing about this is
that the vast majority of politi-
cians never talk about solving

the problem of crime. Any fool
can say, “If you do a crime,
you’ll do the time!” But not
every politician will step off of
his high horse and say, “I’m
willing to try and address the
issue of why so many people
turn to violent crime” and then
do it when he gets elected.
People are not born “violent
criminals.” People turn to vio-
lence and violent crimes as a
way of getting what they want,
just as the so-called “Founding
Fathers” did ' when they
reached North America. In
fact, America is founded on
violent crimes by violent crim-
inals like Christopher
Columbus and Andrew
Jackson. And today the televi-
sion advertises and glarnorizes
every aspect of “violent

crime,” making it look fash- -

ionable to the gullible. If these
slippery politicians were really
honest and really wanted to see
a result other than seeing every
young black man in jail, they
wouldn’t talk about simply
throwing people in jail, but
they’d search for ways to elim-
inate the need for people to
turn to violent crime.

Another big issue is that of
welfare. To be a fashionable
politician, one must know how
to talk that tough talk about
taking people off welfare. The
implication about welfare is
that the majority of people on
it are black (which is false)
and that they are on it due to
sheer laziness and failure to
“pull themselves up by their
own bootstraps” as other
immigrant groups have done in
this country. This is the big lie.
There would have been no
need for welfare or “Great
Society” programs if black
people were not segregated,
kidnapped and terrorized by
violent criminals parading in
white sheets and without
sheets.

Sometimes I get the impres-

sion that when many of these
media personalities and big
politicians speak they actually
believe that people want to live
on welfare as if it were some
type of occupation. Nothing is
further from the truth. Most
people who are on welfare do
not want to be on it. They did
not consciously make the deci-
sion: “Here’s a good occupa-
tion for me. I guess I’ll receive
welfare checks for a living”.
No. If many of the people who
are on welfare would have had
a better opportunity to get a
good job and a good educa-
tion, they would have done it,
but most haven’t had the
opportunity or the advantages
of some of these big-mouthed
personalities.

The history of the United
States, moreover, points to
America as the home of wel-
fare. For 400 years, the United
States survived on the hand-
outs of the enslaved African
masses. Millions of African
men and women were worked
from “can’t see in the morning
to can’t see at night,” and they
received none of their money
for their labor.

What do you think the
Thanksgiving scene is? It’s the
early Americans receiving a
square meal from the generous
Native people of this land; oth-
erwise they probably would
have starved just like that
group at Jamestown. This is
how America received its wel-
fare checks! -

I don’t think some of these
so-called “conservatives” real-
ize how stupid they sound
when they start attacking
everyone else for doing just
what America has done for
years.

I'm not a Republican or a
Democrat. I’m just fed up.

Michael S. Barge is a colum-
nist for The Pitt News major-
ing in Africana Studies/History

  
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
   
  

